description: United Nations Secretary General Antonio Guterres joined in the condemnation of the attack on a UN-run school in the Gaza Strip that killed at least 40 people.
title: UN chief denounces ‘horrific’ attack on UN school in Gaza

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s ambassador to the United Nations on Thursday strongly rejected allegations by the IAEA Board of Governors against the Islamic Republic for its peaceful nuclear program.
title: Iran writes to UN, dismisses E3-crafted IAEA resolution

description: Spain became on Thursday the first European country to ask a United Nations court for permission to join South Africa’s case accusing Israel of genocide in Gaza.
title: Spain applies to join S. Africa’s case at ICJ accusing Israel of genocide

description: TEHRAN - Iran survived a stiff test from Hong Kong, China to walk away with a 4-2 win in their Preliminary Joint Qualification – Round 2 for the FIFA World Cup 2026 and AFC Asian Cup Saudi Arabia 2027 Group E tie on Thursday.
title: Iran defeat Hong Kong in 2026 FIFA World Cup qualifier

description: TEHRAN – Kheybar have secured promotion to 2024/25 Iran’s Persian Gulf Pro League (PGPL) on Wednesday.
title: Kheybar promoted to 2024/25 PGPL

description: TEHRAN – Iran fell short to Brazil 3-1 (25-19, 22-25, 25-16, 25-23) on Thursday in Week 2 of 2024 Volleyball Nations League (VNL) underway in Fukuoka, Japan.
title: Iran beaten by Brazil at 2024 VNL
